trend_summary: Across the time series, low-rise development edges outward from existing streets. Commercial pads expand along the highway, while several wooded lots convert to cul-de-sac housing. New storm-water ponds and parking areas appear, trimming forest cover. Roads widen but no tower blocks arise, leaving a green, medium-density suburban landscape overall.
notable_changes: Progressive commercial strip growth and larger parking lots along the northern highway corridor.
Clearing of central wooded parcels for new residential cul-de-sac subdivisions.
Emergence and enlargement of storm-water/retention ponds in the east-central sector.
Gradual reduction of tree canopy, especially northwest and central areas.
Widening or upgrade of the main north-south arterial road, with added junction complexity.
